   "source": [
    "def format_float(a):\n",
    "    if isinstance(a, float) and (a).is_integer():\n",
    "        return int(a)\n",
    "    else : return a"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "id": "a8d4c1f9-6bee-4e36-b052-89d3185e61eb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def objective(space, clf, X, y, presets, cv=3, scoring='average_precision', fit_params=None):\n",
    "    params = {k: format_float(v) for k, v in {**space, **presets}.items()}\n",
    "    CV = cross_validate(estimator=clf.set_params(**params), X=X, y=y, cv=cv, scoring=scoring, fit_params=fit_params, error_score='raise', return_train_score=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    train_aucpr = np.mean(CV['train_score'])\n",
    "    valid_aucpr = np.mean(CV['test_score'])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x = np.abs(train_aucpr - valid_aucpr)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    delta, std = 0.05, 0.0002\n",
    "    f_val = np.piecewise(x, [x < delta, x >= delta], [valid_aucpr, valid_aucpr*(np.exp(-0.5*((x-delta)**2)/std))])\n",
    "    return {'loss': -f_val, 'status': STATUS_OK}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "id": "8d40148b-e74c-49ca-86d5-3824808e3c4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#presets parameters are the invariant hyperparameters for the model\n",
    "presets = {\n",
    "    'boosting_type' : 'dart',\n",
    "    'objective' : 'binary',\n",
    "    'class_weight' : 'balanced',\n",
    "    'metric' : 'average_precision'\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "592db5d0-3ef9-44c4-a125-174bb60ea8c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# space is the search domain for the objective function optimization\n",
    "space = {\n",
    "    'learning_rate' : hp.loguniform('learning_rate', np.log(0.001), np.log(0.2)),\n",
    "    'num_leaves' : hp.quniform('num_leaves', 8 ,128, 2),\n",
    "    'n_estimators' : hp.quniform('n_estimators', 50, 500, 2),\n",
    "    'max_depth' : hp.quniform('max_depth', 3, 15, 1),\n",
    "    'colsample_bytree' : hp.uniform('colsample_bytree', 0.3, 1.0)\n",
    "}\n",
    "assert ~bool(set(presets.keys()) & set(space.keys()))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "id": "1803551b-14df-4db8-b333-58fd03b8b861",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
